narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Grand Strategy, air strategies, air power's role since WWI
I learned about how the adopting of airpower changed U.S. war strategy and foreign engagement.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Col Oberg was a great instructor. I like how he was open to changing the direction of the course to address the topics we found most interesting. The course was organized, had great readings, and a fair amount of work.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, a great class for a drive-by of American airpower in history. Col Oberg is a kind and understanding lecturer; he caters each class to the interests of the students.
Yes! Great instructor and even cooler students. I hope we get some more non-ROTC kids in the AS courses next semester to hear from different perspectives!
